e haben und welche Publikationsform gewählt wurde, gibt das "Jahrhundertwerk" ein einmalig dichtes Bild der extrem weiten Forschungsinteressen des 18. Jahrhunderts.  aThe "Bio-bibliographical Handbook of Eighteenth Century German Linguistic Scholarship" presents articles on approximately 1600 authors who published works of linguistic interest in German-speaking countries between 1700 and 1800. It will make available for the first time material concerning numerous well-known, but also unknown linguists, which can contribute to an adequate understanding of a fascinating period of linguistic research. - Already published are Vols 1-6.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aLinguisticsxHistoryy18th centuryy18th century. 0aLinguisticsxHistoryy18th century. 0aLinguistsvBiography. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aBrekle, Herbert E., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDobnig-Jülch, Edeltraud, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-DITION: BEST OF GERMAN STUDIESz9783110233933oZDB-23-DGH0 cprintz978348473027440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311093019140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110930191423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110930191/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGH  aZDB-23-DLSc2000d2014